review_blob:
solothurn beerdays 2012.darker brown beer, offwhite head. caramelly, malty, hidden herbal note ( a bit like fresh hay), bittersweet toffee finish.
the brewer himself said its his osterbock, but that now he sells it also under the name frhlingsbock(springbock ) , because easter is 3 week ago;-)
solothurn beerdays. 5.2 alc%. reddish brown. smels hoppy, floral, hidden herbal, has a passion-fruit-like note, has a bittersweet, floral fruity aftertase. good bitterness
really dark beer, little offwhite head.smells caramelly, malty, with hidden hops. tasts bittersweet, but not too sweet, has a hidden fruit-toffee note and  a bittersweet finish.
amber colored beer, smells malty, and hidden floral, has caramel notes, and  a hidden note of hay, a bittersweet finish.
had it on solothurn beerdays 2012. a bock brewed from spelt-grain instead of classical wheat. hazy golden beer. malty , bittersweet, some hops, and  a hidden moschus note.

really dark beer with a little offwhite head. it smells smoky, but malty too, the smokiness is not too dominant. has a smell remembering to a barbecue in the garden. but has some chocolaty notes too. aftertaste is smoky and bittersweet.

hazy s orangeish-golden, but in a icy-colored, belgian wit way. smells herbal-fresh, but fruity too. citrus notes, astonishingly refreshing for a beer who has 7%vol. aftertaste bitter-refreshing, herbal, citrus, and some alcohol.  even if its a strong beer, i can imagine drinking it on a summer evening! but attention! on beginning it seems to have less alcohol than it really has! 
really interesting, i liked it very much
beer_name: Trois Dames la Fraicheur du Soir au Basilic

review_blob: tasted it on solothurn beer-days 2012. darker amber-orangeish hazy beer with an offwhite head. smells  sourish-yeasty-fruity all together. tasts more refreshing than expected by reading the vol%., has citrus notes. aftertaste is a bit hoppier with nice bitterness,some alcohol, and still with some citrus. i liked it! sourish but not too sourish, fruity, not so sweet like other bocks, wow!

amber colored, slightly hazy, only a little white head. smells sweetish and caramelly.tasts way to sweet,  like beer mixed with caramel syrup. with a hint of damp bread. aftertaste sweetish. i didnt like it.
smells and tasts floral, a bit honey-like, with a hidden hint remembering me of elderflower-syrup. a little hint of pine-needles is there too. interesting bittersweetness.

tasted it on solothurn beerdays 
slightly hazy amber colored beer, smells malty and of some floral honey tasts bittersweet and of honey. aftretsste is bittersweet.
an rather interesting not too sweet honey-beer.
smells malty, hoppy, of some sweat, a tannine like hint is also there.tasts hoppy,a bit herbal but with a little hint of honey too.aftertaste nice bittersweetness.,

tasted at the solothurner beerdays 2011.
paler golden beer with some smell of hemp but in a more floral way than other hemp beers i had before. tasts ofhemp with a hint of tropical fruits and flowers. aftertaste hemp, bittersweet, tropical fruits and a hint of pineneedlesinteresting beer.

pale beer, almoust no head. smells  rather hoppy, when drinking it the herbal hoppyness is still there, but a  cereally taste is coming trough. in aftertaste the strange cereally hint is even increasing.

dark amber beer with anoffwhite head, that lets some lacings on the glass. smells of cookies and caramel, with a hint of herbs. then,when drinking,it grows  even a bit more herbal. aftertaste is bittersweetness, with more wight on bitterness than sweetness, and there are some cookies too. my prefered beer of the 3 beers from this brewery( end november 2010 or in the beginning of december, their dark bock(saisonal) will be released,  i want to try it!)

hazy golden beer, white head. smells spicy(clove), a bit fruity, and of almonds. in mouth, spicy too, with a floral hint, and something special  marzipan-like( more marzipan than normal almonds). aftertaste spice and almonds.

freihof lager
slightly hazy golden beer. smells malty, hoppy, of some cookies. tasts hoppy, bittersweet, cereally. aftertaste is bittersweet, and of fresh cereals.

my bottle says 5.0%vol. lagerbeer. pale beer, with a little, not long lasting white head. smells malty, cereally, of some hops. there is even a hidden hint of something that remembers me to t urine-scale( the chalky residues in not very well cleaned wc s urinstein in german) aargh!!   tasts malty, cereally, a bit sweetish. like cheap low-quality maize-pops. aftertsat hops, cerals, bittersweetness. aaargh!!
darker amber beer with an offwhite head. smells malty with a corriander-like sicyness and fruits. tasts malty, ocorriander-like, of some pears aftertaste malty, corriandery, bittersweet
smells of hops and like tropical cfruits but herbal too. tasts bitter-fruity-has really a a taste like passion-fruit, but herbal again. aftertaste bitter-fruity-herbal in one.wow!!!!

had it in the -new yorks food company- besides the railwaystation of lucerne, switzerland. pale golden, white head lasts not long. smells rather hoppy and a bit cerally. tasts more hoppy than cereally. aftertase hoppy bitterness. not a beer with much different aromes and tasts, but has a good hoppyness. so what the label says is rather right, its made to drink with asian food ( but i had a burger, not indian food).

clearer amber colored beer. smells of malt, caramel, some hops. tasts malty, of some caramel, some hops. aftertaste is bittersweet. not bad, but not overwhelming, could be more tastefull. other beers from belhaven are better.

had it under the name augenbraueri hiver 1. amber colored beer with a good head. smells malty, of caramel, hops, perhaps a bit floral/fruity and tasts rather hoppy too. in aftertaste some bittersweetness and hops.

orangeish hazy beer, but not so dark than expected when reading the deScription of the brewery. smells yeasty and bready. tasts yeasty, cerally, refreshing, but not so fruity. a bit of spicyness. aftertaste bready, cookie-like.

amber beer. smells of malt and some caramel. tasts malty and of some caramel, a bit like cookie, and has a sweetish hint of artificial fruit-bonbons(toffees). aftertaste is bittersweet. could be more tasty. not bad, but not special. with such a name, you expect more taste.

dark reddish brown beer, offwhite head.  smells malty, with  a hint of dried plums, and a bit like port. tasts malty, bittersweet, of dried  plums. aftertaste bitterness and  a fruitpunch-like hint and some good warmth
